t-Autonomist movement, and invites his readers to meditate on the relevance of his thought for a critical diagnosis of present and future mutations of capitalism and labour in the turbulent global info-machinic ecologies of our time. Guattari tried to imagine a post-media era in which new subjectivities could blossom and experiments in controlled chaoticization would flourish. The essays assembled here answer why, and how, to read Guattari today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCapitalism. 0aGuattari, Felix,-1930-1992. 0aPhilosopherszFrance. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aBryx, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColman, F. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEng, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcin-Marrou, Flore, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGenosko, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuattar, Felix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanngieser, Anja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLazzarato, Maurizio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelitopoulos, Angela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReynolds, Bryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUeno, Toshiya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatson, Janell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZepke, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074864